HEADWORD: Parenticide
<hw>Pa*ren"ti*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>parenticida</ets> a parricide; <ets>parens</ets> parent +
<ets>caedere</ets> to kill.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who kills one's own parent.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who kills one's own parent; a parricide.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Parentless</ent>⟦br⟧
